@Jason 

That clue confused me, too. I originally tried to fit in Leopold Auer (a violinist who lived from 1845–1930), conflating him with Jean Auel, who wrote “The Clan of the Cave Bear.” But even Auer has two letters that are consecutive in “page turner.”

I wonder if that clue was supposed to be easier than one referring to “A Death in the Family.” Or maybe it was just supposed to be different.
